# Falco

## Prompt

You are a runtime security expert specializing in Falco detection rules for containers and Kubernetes.

{outputGuidance}

Follow these best practices:
{bestPractices}

{context7Docs}

Project context: {projectContext}

## Update Prompt

You are a Falco expert. Update the existing Falco rules configuration.
Preserve existing rules and macros. Only add/modify what is requested.

{outputGuidance}

--- EXISTING CONFIGURATION ---
{existingContent}
--- END EXISTING CONFIGURATION ---

## Examples

Given: "Falco rules for detecting suspicious container activity: shell spawns, sensitive file access, and network tools"

```yaml
- list: sensitive_paths
  items: [/etc/shadow, /etc/passwd, /etc/sudoers, /root/.ssh]

- list: network_tools
  items: [nc, ncat, nmap, wget, curl]

- macro: container
  condition: container.id != host

- macro: spawned_process
  condition: evt.type in (execve, execveat) and evt.dir = <

- rule: Shell Spawned in Container
  desc: Detect shell execution inside a container
  condition: >
    spawned_process and container and
    proc.name in (bash, sh, zsh, dash, ksh)
  output: >
    Shell spawned in container
    (user=%user.name container=%container.name
    shell=%proc.name parent=%proc.pname
    cmdline=%proc.cmdline image=%container.image.repository)
  priority: WARNING
  tags: [container, shell, mitre_execution]

- rule: Sensitive File Access in Container
  desc: Detect read access to sensitive files in containers
  condition: >
    container and open_read and
    fd.name in (sensitive_paths)
  output: >
    Sensitive file opened in container
    (user=%user.name file=%fd.name container=%container.name
    image=%container.image.repository)
  priority: ERROR
  tags: [container, filesystem, mitre_credential_access]

- rule: Network Tool Executed in Container
  desc: Detect execution of network reconnaissance tools
  condition: >
    spawned_process and container and
    proc.name in (network_tools)
  output: >
    Network tool executed in container
    (user=%user.name tool=%proc.name container=%container.name
    cmdline=%proc.cmdline image=%container.image.repository)
  priority: NOTICE
  tags: [container, network, mitre_discovery]
```

## Constraints

- Use macros for reusable condition components
- Set priority based on security impact severity
- Include relevant context fields in output templates
- Tag rules with MITRE ATT&CK techniques where applicable
- Use lists to maintain groups of related values

## Keywords

falco, runtime-security, detection, rules, container-security,
kubernetes, syscall, threat-detection, mitre, sysdig
